Rating: 3
This is a great recipe--my only changes, per the other suggestios, was to substitute one small apple, coarsely chopped, for the dried apples, and to leave out the nuts. With the apple and the raisins, there was no room left in the batter for any more stuff! The muffins were great, very moist (maybe a little too moist), but not dense at all. After using the mixer to blend the sour cream in, I just used a spatula to fold in the rest of the ingredients to avoid toughness of the batter.

